<gpx creator="StravaGPX" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/1 http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/1/gpx.xsd" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/1">
 <metadata>
  <name>Heart Shaped Boxford</name>
  <desc>Looking for a Valentine's Day ride? This ride up to Boxford and then back down the coast is one of the nicer northern routes. The commute in/out of the city through Wakefield can be challenging during rush hour but otherwise the roads are nice. There is some gravel around mile 50 but it is short and doable on a road bike.</desc>
  <author>
   <name>Tim Beaver</name>
   <link href="https://www.strava.com/athletes/23022900"/>
  </author>
  <copyright author="OpenStreetMap contributors">
   <year>2020</year>
   <license>https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright</license>
  </copyright>
  <link href="https://www.strava.com/routes/3137853059639910618"/>
 </metadata>
